In the discussion, James sought to reframe the work of IMT around New York Community Trust's goals, emphasizing both offensive and defensive strategies in the context of community-focused building performance policies. The offensive goals highlight IMT's proactive efforts to leverage past achievements and foster collaborations with local governments and CBOs, aiming for equitable building decarbonization. Notable engagements include partnerships in Chicago, Washington DC, and Philadelphia for co-governance structures, energy efficiency upgrades, and aligning policies with community needs. The defense goals emphasize safeguarding climate justice progress through trusted guidance and community engagement frameworks. IMT also focuses on providing education and legal support to ensure effective policy implementation and defense against challenges, collaborating with the Public Health Law Center for pivotal legal strategies. This synthesis encapsulates the critical roles of collaboration and empowerment in driving sustainability efforts.
